<section version="5.0"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook http://www.docbook.org/xml/5.0/xsd/docbook.xsd"
    xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
    xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mth="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"
    xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <title>Manage legend sets</title>
    <para>You can create your own legend sets to ensure meaningful maps. </para>
    <note>
        <para>Continuous legends are supposed to end and start on the same value, for example 0-50
            and 50-80. The GIS app automatically take care of
            <?oxy_comment_start author="Home" timestamp="20160413T120439+0200" comment="Of what?"?>this<?oxy_comment_end?>.
            Do not try to do this yourself by setting legends to for example 0-50 and 51-80. This
            will cause a usually unwanted gap in your legend set.</para>
    </note>
    <section>
        <title>Create a new legend set</title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Legends</emphasis>.</para>
                <para> The <emphasis role="bold">Legend sets</emphasis> dialog box opens.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Add new</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Legend set name</emphasis> box, type the name you
                    want to give the legend set.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Create the legends you want to have in your legend set:</para>
                <orderedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Legend name</emphasis> field, type the
                            legend name.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Select <emphasis role="bold">Start/end value</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Select <emphasis role="bold">Symbolizer</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Add legend</emphasis>.</para>
                        <para>The legend is added to <emphasis role="bold">Current
                                legends</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><?oxy_comment_start author="CPersson" timestamp="20160420T143924+0200" comment="At next release, add x-refs."?>Repeat<?oxy_comment_end?>
                            until you have created all the legends you need.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </orderedlist>
                <example>
                    <title>Vaccination coverage legends</title>
                    <para>
                        <table frame="all">
                            <title>Example of vaccination coverage legends</title>
                            <tgroup cols="4">
                                <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                                <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                                <colspec colname="c3" colnum="3" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                                <colspec colname="c4" colnum="4" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                                <thead>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry>Legend name</entry>
                                        <entry>Start value</entry>
                                        <entry>End value</entry>
                                        <entry>Symbolizer</entry>
                                    </row>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry>Low bad</entry>
                                        <entry>0</entry>
                                        <entry>50</entry>
                                        <entry>red</entry>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry>Medium</entry>
                                        <entry>50</entry>
                                        <entry>80</entry>
                                        <entry>yellow</entry>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry>High good</entry>
                                        <entry>80</entry>
                                        <entry>100</entry>
                                        <entry>green</entry>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry>Too high</entry>
                                        <entry>100</entry>
                                        <entry>1000</entry>
                                        <entry>grey</entry>
                                    </row>
                                </tbody>
                            </tgroup>
                        </table>
                    </para>
                </example>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Create</emphasis>.</para>
                <note>
                    <para>If your legend set has overlapping legends (for example 0-50 and 40-80)
                        you will not be allowed to proceed. If your legend set has a gap between the
                        legends (for example 0-50 and 60-80) you will get a warning, but are allowed
                        to proceed.</para>
                </note>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Change a legend set</title>
        <para>
            <orderedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Legends</emphasis>. </para>
                    <para>The <emphasis role="bold">Legend sets</emphasis> dialog box opens.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click the edit icon next to the legend set you want to modify.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Current legends</emphasis> list, click the
                        edit icon next to the legend you want to modify.</para>
                    <para>The <emphasis role="bold">Edit legend</emphasis> dialog box opens.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Modify the parameters and click <emphasis role="bold"
                        >Update</emphasis>.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Legend sets</emphasis> dialog box, click
                            <emphasis role="bold">Update</emphasis>.</para>
                </listitem>
            </orderedlist>
        </para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Delete a legend set</title>
        <para>
            <orderedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Legends</emphasis>. </para>
                    <para>The <emphasis role="bold">Legend sets</emphasis> dialog box opens.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click the delete icon next to the legend set you want to delete.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">OK</emphasis> to confirm that you want to
                        delete the legend set.</para>
                </listitem>
            </orderedlist>
        </para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Assign a legend set to indicator or data
            <?oxy_comment_start author="Home" timestamp="20160414T113214+0200" comment="At next revision, add x-ref to relevant topic."?>element<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
        <para>You can assign a legend set to an indicator or a data element in the Indicator/Data
            element module. This legend set will then be automatically selected when such an
            indicator/data element is selected in the GIS.</para>
    </section>    
</section>
